title: It's RAININ' MEN
body_text:
DODGEBALL 133 Results
Battle Royal Series
: Sophomore Attempt!
Battle Royal Contestants
included Alison Bertsch, Alysha Kelly, Bobby Bonney, Bobby Vetrano, John Tronolone, Justin Pierce
(Runner-up)
, Lauren Stopa, Mike Butler, Mike "Sputz" Krott, and the eventual winner,
Ryan Letsche
. The former two-time season finale headliner was able to overcome the deadly Krott/Pierce alliance during this physically draining free-for-all. This was just another crowning achievement in the storied career of the wily veteran.
Flash Results by Game
CAR WRECKERS: 1, 4, 5
MOMMA WRECKERS: 2, 3
The element of surprise - varied gametypes, torrential downpour, debuting and returning superstars - played a huge role in this 133rd spectacular.
The Rules
: Switched numerous times between classic two-team,
Prison Ball
, the rare
Secret "Captain"
, and a
Prison Ball
-
Secret "Captains"
combination.
The Match
: The CAR WRECKERS defeated The MOMMA WRECKERS, 3 to 2.
Moments & Stars
: Alison Bertsch pelting a dashing Molly Miller in the leg; newbie Charlie Podesta's powerful throws; Mike Edwards's match-winning eliminations on Chris Adams and John Tronolone; the intense downpour to conclude the night
Attendance
: 26 competitors, comprised of 19 men and 7 women.
New Players
: Allen Griner, Charlie Podesta, Gail Garbarine, Tim Hart
Other Notes
: DODGEBALL 133 was the 27th
Wet War
; the
Secret "Captain"
stipulation was last featured at DODGEBALL 50 in August 2006.
Coming Up Next
: DODGEBALL 134 presents the final
Battle Royal
of this three-week period with the victor earning complete creative control over the event. Plus, listen closely for the DODGEBALL 135 match-up scheduled for April 26!
Still to Come
... The mega-sized DODGEBALL CXL encounter between two of the biggest names to ever compete, Justin Wolf and Juan Londono, is coming May 31.
body_html:
DODGEBALL 133 Results
Battle Royal Series: Sophomore Attempt!

Battle Royal Contestants included Alison Bertsch, Alysha Kelly, Bobby Bonney, Bobby Vetrano, John Tronolone, Justin Pierce (Runner-up), Lauren Stopa, Mike Butler, Mike "Sputz" Krott, and the eventual winner, Ryan Letsche. The former two-time season finale headliner was able to overcome the deadly Krott/Pierce alliance during this physically draining free-for-all. This was just another crowning achievement in the storied career of the wily veteran.

Flash Results by Game
CAR WRECKERS: 1, 4, 5
MOMMA WRECKERS: 2, 3

The element of surprise - varied gametypes, torrential downpour, debuting and returning superstars - played a huge role in this 133rd spectacular.

The Rules: Switched numerous times between classic two-team, Prison Ball, the rare Secret "Captain", and a Prison Ball-Secret "Captains" combination.
The Match: The CAR WRECKERS defeated The MOMMA WRECKERS, 3 to 2.
Moments & Stars: Alison Bertsch pelting a dashing Molly Miller in the leg; newbie Charlie Podesta's powerful throws; Mike Edwards's match-winning eliminations on Chris Adams and John Tronolone; the intense downpour to conclude the night
Attendance: 26 competitors, comprised of 19 men and 7 women.
New Players: Allen Griner, Charlie Podesta, Gail Garbarine, Tim Hart
Other Notes: DODGEBALL 133 was the 27th Wet War; the Secret "Captain" stipulation was last featured at DODGEBALL 50 in August 2006.

Coming Up Next: DODGEBALL 134 presents the final Battle Royal of this three-week period with the victor earning complete creative control over the event. Plus, listen closely for the DODGEBALL 135 match-up scheduled for April 26!

Still to Come ... The mega-sized DODGEBALL CXL encounter between two of the biggest names to ever compete, Justin Wolf and Juan Londono, is coming May 31.
